      "raw_text": "With the signatures of 12S of tie\nmost prominent citizens Of Spokane\naffixed to affidavits in support of\nopposition to the change of venue\napplied for in the Filigno-Gurley\nFlynn trial. the prosecuting attor-\nney is prepared to fight all efforts\nof the [. w. w. attorneys to secure\nthe 3moval of the case from tie\nSpokane county courts.\n\n\nThe affidavits, as prepared by\nDeputy Prosecutor Don F. Kizer\nand circulated by Captain of Detec-\ntives Martin Burns and Deputy\nSheriff Jim Logan, are to the effect\nthat the signers believe that the\nnewspaper comment during the I.\nw. w. trouble has not prejudiced\nthem against G. l.. Filigno and\nElizabeth Gurley Flynn Jones,\nwhose trial on a conspiracy charge\ncomes up before Judge Fl. L. Ken\nnan tomorrow."
    }
